{"parse":{"title":"Command","pageid":1465,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>5-2-120</b>\n</p><p>An input variable established by means external to and independent of the automatic control system which is intended to determine the value of the controlled variable.\n</p><p><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:Ch5_Fig2.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/f/fb/Ch5_Fig2.jpg/400px-Ch5_Fig2.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"220\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/f/fb/Ch5_Fig2.jpg/600px-Ch5_Fig2.jpg 1.5x, /wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/f/fb/Ch5_Fig2.jpg/800px-Ch5_Fig2.jpg 2x\"></a></span>\n</p><p>Figure 2 - Block diagram of automatic control system (5-2-045) incorporating a closed loop (5-2-080)\n</p><p>Reference: ANSI (modified)\n</p><p>Note:: The French word \"commande\" is generally used to mean control.\n</p><p><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<i>Please note that this is the term as it stands in the original <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> Dictionary edition (1970-1989)</i>\n<br>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php?title=Command_5-2-120&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Command 5-2-120 (page does not exist)\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - AISM\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260615104554\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.052 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.063 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 60/1000000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 776/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 203/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 4/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   16.564      1 -total\n 75.38%   12.486      1 Template:Languages\n 48.19%    7.982      4 Template:Languages/Lang\n 23.30%    3.860      1 Template:IALAFooter\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki_iala_dictionary_1_41:pcache:idhash:1465-0!canonical and timestamp 20260615104554 and revision id 3867. Rendering was triggered because: page-view\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"5.2_Control_Systems"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Alphabetical_Index"},{"sortkey":"","*":"IALA_Dictionary_1970-89_Edition"}]}}